                            <comment id="12611717" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 8 Jul 2008 17:50:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll see how faster we can get. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This code will also be modified with the integration of ZK.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12611755" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 8 Jul 2008 19:14:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I tried something else. The MetaScanner thread sleeps 60 seconds by default. For a small cluster, it means that it will take at least 1 minute to start up. I did a little dirty hack that puts that time at 5 seconds as long as the meta regions are not scanned then it restores the configured time. My modifications enable other hacks like this one since I modified Sleeper.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Clint, try it out and see if it fits your needs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12611761" author="clint.morgan" created="Tue, 8 Jul 2008 19:23:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah this worked great: took startup time from 60 sec to 8 sec.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12611793" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 8 Jul 2008 20:55:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The initialScan has poor chances of being called with metaRegionsToScan filled. So the optimization will do nothing for a lot of people (and if you have a big cluster, starting it will be long enough for other reasons). So this modification is out of scope in this jira.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Something doable would be to clear the ROOT table.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12611819" author="stack" created="Tue, 8 Jul 2008 21:51:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;On current patch:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Perhaps make an accessor rather than change the following to be protected?  +  protected final Sleeper sleeper;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Why have a nextPeriod?  Why not just have a setPeriod?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Otherwise, good so far J-D.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12612072" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 9 Jul 2008 13:11:40 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Why have a nextPeriod? Why not just have a setPeriod?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In context :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void sleep(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt; startTime) {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.stop.get()) {
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt;;
    }
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt; now = &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;System&lt;/span&gt;.currentTimeMillis();
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt; waitTime = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.period - (now - startTime);
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (waitTime &amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.period) {
      LOG.warn(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Calculated wait time &amp;gt; &quot;&lt;/span&gt; + &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.period +
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;; setting to &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.period: &quot;&lt;/span&gt; + &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;System&lt;/span&gt;.currentTimeMillis() + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;, &quot;&lt;/span&gt; +
        startTime);
    }
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (waitTime &amp;gt; 0) {
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Thread&lt;/span&gt;.sleep(waitTime);
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt; slept = &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;System&lt;/span&gt;.currentTimeMillis() - now;
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (slept &amp;gt; (10 * &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.period)) {
          LOG.warn(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;We slept &quot;&lt;/span&gt; + slept + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;ms, ten times longer than scheduled: &quot;&lt;/span&gt; +
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.period);
        }
      } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt;(InterruptedException iex) {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// We we interrupted because we&apos;re meant to stop?  If not, just
&lt;/span&gt;        &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;continue&lt;/span&gt; ignoring the interruption
&lt;/span&gt;        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.stop.get()) {
          &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt;;
        }
      }
    }
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.nextPeriod != &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.period)
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.period = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.nextPeriod;
  }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not too sure of what would happen if the period is changed during the execution of this method.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12612138" author="apurtell" created="Wed, 9 Jul 2008 15:11:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Scanning meta ahead of schedule on startup could be done by just interrupting the MetaScanner thread at the right point in the startup sequence. Maybe that is enough? &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
master.regionManager.metaScannerThread.interrupt();
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12612297" author="stack" created="Wed, 9 Jul 2008 21:46:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;J-D: Andrew&apos;s suggestion sounds cleaner if it will work for you.  Otherwise, in your code, looks like we could just read this.period once at the start of the method into a local variable and use the local variable rather than this.period thereafter.  Should probably change this.period to be volatile so threads see changes promptly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Good stuff.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12612497" author="jdcryans" created="Thu, 10 Jul 2008 13:45:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Followed Andrew&apos;s suggestion. The patch resulting is really simple, the hardest part being to have the interrupt at the right place.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks buddy!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12612586" author="stack" created="Thu, 10 Jul 2008 17:46:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.  Thanks J-D.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We&apos;re not actually rinsing SERVER and STARTCODE &amp;#8211; its hard to do for .META. case as J-D states above &amp;#8211; but this patch seems to get the same effect by forcing the first scan.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
